The paper discusses the use of Holographic Multiple Input Multiple Output Surface (HMIMOS) for future wireless networks, which involves the use of hardware architectures for reconfigurable metasurfaces. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-categories, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), electromagnetics (cs.EM), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
